feature request: enumerate iterator similar to python

An enumerate iterator would provide the functionality of these zippered
iterators:

  for (value, i) in zip(myIter, 1..) {
    // do something with i and value...
  }
  forall (value, i) in zip(myIter, 1..) {
    // do something with i and value...
  }

For example:

  for (value, i) in enumerate(myIter) {
    // do something with i and value...
  }
  forall (value, i) in enumerate(myIter) {
    // do something with i and value...
  }

Programmers accustomed to using python's enumerate iterator, but not yet
familiar with chapel's zippered iterators, would find this useful.
